<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B18FF86FF6CF893FB44D8CD" blockId="42.[192,1217,1859,1883]" lastBlockId="43.[192,1210,195,219]" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B18FF87FF6CF893FE84DF4D" bold="true" box="[192,378,1859,1883]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">
<typeStatus id="54EE88727B18FF87FF6CF893FEFBDF4D" box="[192,261,1859,1883]" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">Type</typeStatus>
locality.
</emphasis>
Neal Spring, north rim of Grand Canyon, Coconino County, 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B18FF87FBFBF893FB42DF4D" box="[1111,1212,1859,1883]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="42" pageNumber="41">Arizona</collectingRegion>
. 
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B19FF86FF6CFF13FE64D8CD" bold="true" box="[192,410,195,219]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">
<typeStatus id="54EE88727B19FF86FF6CFF13FEFBD8CD" box="[192,261,195,219]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">Type</typeStatus>
label data.
</emphasis>
I have not examined the label data associated with this specimen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B19FF86FF6CFED3FD84D94D" blockId="43.[192,1440,259,347]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B19FF86FF6CFED3FD21D90D" bold="true" box="[192,735,259,283]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">Identification, taxonomy, and variation.</emphasis>
Adults are bright orange-yellow dorsally and dark basally. Adult wingspan ranges from 
<quantity id="4CAD9B357B19FF86FDB2FEF3FD64D92D" box="[542,666,291,315]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="43" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="55.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="50.0">50-60 mm</quantity>
. This subspecies somewhat resembles 
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B19FF86FBC5FEF4FB03D92D" box="[1129,1277,291,315]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">
S. h. 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B19FF86FB09FEF3FB03D92D" authorityName="Edwards" authorityYear="1879" box="[1189,1277,291,315]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argynnis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chitone">chitone</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
but is always silver on the ventral hindwing spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B19FF86FF6CFE53FC7FD98D" blockId="43.[192,897,387,411]" box="[192,897,387,411]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B19FF86FF6CFE53FEE1D98D" bold="true" box="[192,287,387,411]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">Range.</emphasis>
Kaibab Plateau, near the Grand Canyon, 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B19FF86FCB4FE53FC82D98D" box="[792,892,387,411]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">Arizona</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B19FF86FF6CFE13FC30D9CD" blockId="43.[192,974,451,475]" box="[192,974,451,475]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B19FF86FF6CFE13FE96D9CD" bold="true" box="[192,360,451,475]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">Life history.</emphasis>
Adults are active in secluded draws along springs.
</paragraph>
